{
  "texts": [
    "The existence of simplification was thus confirmed in the interpreted speeches but partially in the translated texts.",
    "To recap, simplification in human translations has been investigated in different translated languages by using various lexical and syntactic measures.",
    "However, the influence of genre on simplification features has not been thoroughly examined, despite that some studies have used materials from multiple genres such as Xiao and Yue (2009), Liu and Afzaal (2021), and Liu et al. (2022).",
    "In addition, the results regarding simplification in human translations have been somewhat inconclusive at different linguistic levels.",
    "Simplification in machine translations."
  ]
}